00:58:15,973 --> 00:58:17,452
-Martin!
-Don't be frightened.

510
00:58:18,573 --> 00:58:20,006
Oh, my God.

511
00:58:21,653 --> 00:58:23,211
What happened?

512
00:58:26,573 --> 00:58:28,609
I didn't know where else to go.

513
00:58:31,053 --> 00:58:33,806
You need your medication.
We have to get you back.

514
00:58:35,173 --> 00:58:38,290
There's no medication for what I have.

515
00:58:38,533 --> 00:58:39,443
What?

516
00:58:39,653 --> 00:58:41,405
There never was.

517
00:58:45,853 --> 00:58:48,208
They were all just. . .

518
00:58:49,333 --> 00:58:51,005
. . .waiting for. . . .

519
00:58:51,253 --> 00:58:52,402
For this. . .

520
00:58:53,133 --> 00:58:54,088
. . .to happen.

521
00:58:58,253 --> 00:58:59,652
I had to see you, Beth.

522
00:59:03,053 --> 00:59:04,771
Do you want me to go?

523
00:59:09,053 --> 00:59:10,042
No.

524
00:59:12,373 --> 00:59:14,204
Then help me.

525
00:59:18,453 --> 00:59:19,488
Please?

526
00:59:22,413 --> 00:59:23,402
Yes.

527
00:59:33,333 --> 00:59:34,812
All right, let's go.

528
00:59:42,333 --> 00:59:45,609
Thomas, go upstairs.
Chris, help out.

529
00:59:47,613 --> 00:59:49,729
(CAT MEOWS)

530
00:59:49,933 --> 00:59:52,083
-Anything upstairs, Thomas?
THOMAS: Only a cat.

531
00:59:52,333 --> 00:59:53,402
Jesus!

532
00:59:54,013 --> 00:59:56,402
Go check the dock.
Chris, go with him.

533
00:59:59,453 --> 01:00:00,408
The girl?

534
01:00:00,653 --> 01:00:02,006
SCORBY:
She went with him.

535
01:00:02,253 --> 01:00:04,403
Well, get back here
as soon as you can.

536
01:00:05,133 --> 01:00:08,887
Yes. Don't worry, sir, we'll get him.
It's just a matter of time.

537
01:00:09,453 --> 01:00:12,013
That, sadly, is a luxury
we don't have.

538
01:01:06,379 --> 01:01:07,732
STATHIS:
Go away.

539
01:01:09,979 --> 01:01:13,130
-We have to talk to you, sir.
-I said piss off!

540
01:01:16,419 --> 01:01:18,728
Seth Brundle was my father.

541
01:01:38,299 --> 01:01:40,529
Striking family resemblance.

542
01:01:41,979 --> 01:01:43,935
Little big for 5 years old.

543
01:01:44,139 --> 01:01:46,733
I have a chromosomal malfunction.

544
01:01:46,939 --> 01:01:50,648
I'm growing at an accelerated rate.

545
01:01:51,539 --> 01:01:53,530
No shit? That's fascinating.

546
01:01:55,379 --> 01:01:56,528
Well. . . .

547
01:01:58,019 --> 01:01:59,577
Listen, it's been great.

548
01:01:59,819 --> 01:02:01,730
Stop by again some time.

549
01:02:08,619 --> 01:02:10,735
Perhaps I should invite you in.

550
01:02:12,619 --> 01:02:15,577
I saw you on the videotape.

551
01:02:15,819 --> 01:02:17,138
Don't sit there!

552
01:02:22,219 --> 01:02:24,449
You were there
the night my father died.

553
01:02:24,699 --> 01:02:27,532
He was working on a cure.

554
01:02:31,379 --> 01:02:35,531
That's why you dragged yourself
out here? To find out about a cure?

555
01:02:35,779 --> 01:02:37,337
You're my only hope.

556
01:02:43,579 --> 01:02:45,012
Oh, kid. . .

557
01:02:45,259 --> 01:02:49,457
. . .the last thing I am
is anybody's hope.

558
01:02:49,819 --> 01:02:52,333
You really don't want
to hear about this.

559
01:02:53,619 --> 01:02:55,132
I have to know.

560
01:02:57,019 --> 01:03:00,978
Brundle stole my girl.

561
01:03:01,539 --> 01:03:02,858
Your mother.

562
01:03:03,099 --> 01:03:05,932
Got her pregnant, caused her death.

563
01:03:06,499 --> 01:03:09,218
Dissolved my hand and my foot
with fly vomit.

564
01:03:09,459 --> 01:03:12,337
I had no love for the man.

565
01:03:15,019 --> 01:03:16,532
He bugged me.

566
01:03:19,139 --> 01:03:22,734
As for the cure he was working on. . .

567
01:03:25,339 --> 01:03:27,728
. . .he dragged your mother. . .

568
01:03:28,699 --> 01:03:31,372
. . .kicking and screaming
into that telepod. . .

569
01:03:31,619 --> 01:03:36,534
. . .that they might be fused together
in one beautiful body.

570
01:03:37,019 --> 01:03:40,648
So your mother blew his brains out
with a shotgun.

571
01:03:41,819 --> 01:03:42,854
There's your cure.

572
01:03:46,299 --> 01:03:47,288
Go away.

573
01:03:47,499 --> 01:03:50,935
You bastard!
Where's your compassion?

574
01:03:51,379 --> 01:03:54,530
I had to give it up.
It cost me an arm and a leg.

575
01:03:59,099 --> 01:04:00,930
It cost you more than that.

576
01:04:04,619 --> 01:04:06,814
Your father was right about one thing.

577
01:04:07,019 --> 01:04:09,931
If there's a cure, it has something
to do with those pods.

578
01:04:12,019 --> 01:04:13,338
That. . . .

579
01:04:13,939 --> 01:04:15,531
They won't work.

580
01:04:16,419 --> 01:04:18,728
You're a bad liar, kid.

581
01:04:19,019 --> 01:04:21,408
If you found the answer,
use it.

582
01:04:21,619 --> 01:04:22,972
Martin, did you find--?

583
01:04:23,219 --> 01:04:26,529
It's nothing I can use.
So forget it.

584
01:04:27,099 --> 01:04:28,214
Let's go.

585
01:04:28,699 --> 01:04:31,133
You should talk some sense
to your friend.

586
01:04:33,419 --> 01:04:35,330
They'll be looking for your car.

587
01:04:35,539 --> 01:04:37,530
My Jeep's in the garage.

588
01:04:39,099 --> 01:04:40,134
Just. . .

589
01:04:41,699 --> 01:04:43,132
. . .get out.

590
01:04:53,099 --> 01:04:56,694
-Let me just call Bartok.
-No, I'm not going back there.

591
01:04:56,899 --> 01:04:58,935
He can help.
I'll tell him about the tele--

592
01:04:59,179 --> 01:05:02,091
-That's a dead end.
-You haven't told me why.

593
01:05:02,339 --> 01:05:05,968
The only way I could save myself
would be to sacrifice another life.

594
01:05:48,539 --> 01:05:50,609
(CLEARS THROAT)

595
01:05:52,579 --> 01:05:55,332
I'd like a room, please.

596
01:05:57,699 --> 01:05:59,178
All I have is a queen size.

597
01:05:59,419 --> 01:06:01,535
Is that okay?

598
01:06:01,779 --> 01:06:03,337
That'll be fine.

599
01:06:09,219 --> 01:06:11,130
Cash in advance.

600
01:06:14,419 --> 01:06:18,048
Brundle vanished late last night
with co-worker, Beth Logan.

601
01:06:18,299 --> 01:06:21,655
There has been speculation
that Ms. Logan was kidnapped...

602
01:06:21,899 --> 01:06:23,969
...but this has yet to be confirmed.

603
01:06:24,819 --> 01:06:25,808
Number nine. . .

604
01:06:26,619 --> 01:06:27,938
. . .Miss. . .

605
01:06:29,379 --> 01:06:30,937
. . .Smith.

606
01:06:33,019 --> 01:06:34,338
Martin?

607
01:06:36,019 --> 01:06:37,930
Martin!

608
01:06:38,139 --> 01:06:39,936
Martin!

609
01:06:42,379 --> 01:06:43,528
Martin!

610
01:06:43,779 --> 01:06:44,894
(HORN HONKS)

611
01:06:55,619 --> 01:06:57,735
Martin, stop.

612
01:07:03,619 --> 01:07:06,531
Please don't run away from me.

613
01:07:10,379 --> 01:07:12,051
I don't know what to do.

614
01:07:12,819 --> 01:07:14,138
I don't either.

615
01:07:16,139 --> 01:07:19,734
Martin, I'm not gonna leave you.

616
01:07:21,179 --> 01:07:22,328
No.

617
01:07:33,259 --> 01:07:36,649
(BUG ZAPPER BUZZES)

618
01:07:49,819 --> 01:07:52,333
MARTIN:
How peaceful that light is.

619
01:07:56,499 --> 01:07:58,137
Compelling.

620
01:08:01,819 --> 01:08:02,934
What?

621
01:08:13,459 --> 01:08:14,528
You. . .

622
01:08:15,219 --> 01:08:16,538
. . .should go.

623
01:08:24,619 --> 01:08:26,132
You need help.

624
01:08:27,219 --> 01:08:29,938
You don't think I can take care
of myself?

625
01:08:33,419 --> 01:08:34,738
No.

626
01:08:36,939 --> 01:08:38,531
You can't walk.

627
01:08:46,579 --> 01:08:47,773
You're getting worse.

628
01:08:48,219 --> 01:08:50,733
I'm getting better.

629
01:08:52,099 --> 01:08:53,498
My body. . .

630
01:08:53,739 --> 01:08:54,967
. . .is growing. . .

631
01:08:56,539 --> 01:08:57,972
. . .stronger.

632
01:09:00,019 --> 01:09:02,328
I feel good.

633
01:09:02,699 --> 01:09:04,735
You don't know what you're saying.

634
01:09:05,379 --> 01:09:07,734
I do know what I'm saying.

635
01:09:10,779 --> 01:09:15,375
Until now, I've been nothing more
than an open wound.

636
01:09:15,619 --> 01:09:17,211
Defenseless. . .

637
01:09:17,419 --> 01:09:19,933
. . .weak, vulnerable.

638
01:09:20,619 --> 01:09:21,688
